HEADWORD: Poetaster
<hw>Po"et*as`ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An inferior
rhymer, or writer of verses; a dabbler in poetic art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The talk of forgotten <qex>poetasters</qex>.</q>
